Hormone replacement therapy raises women's risk of getting brain a tumour by 30 per cent, according to researchers.

Women who take medication to relieve the symptoms of the menopause could therefore be putting themselves in danger of cancer and other illnesses.

For those who use HRT over a period of time, the risk of developing a tumour is as high as 70 per cent.

